The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 21: A Delhi court has advised the two factions of Ranbaxy founder late Bhai Mohan Singh?s family, who are fighting over the property of the patriarch, to arrive at a compromise keeping in view the interests of the employees. On a defamation complaint filed by Max group chairman Analjit Singh, additional chief metropolitan magistrate Kamini Lau observed that the offences alleged by the opposing factions were compoundable in nature.

 New Delhi, July 21: Chevron?s country head Jeet Bindra was today nominated to the board of Reliance Petroleum. Earlier, Chevron picked up a 5 per cent equity in RPL.

 Chennai, July 21: Sebi will soon issue a regulation to ensure that companies maintain a ?quiet period? before and during the launch of their IPOs. This will prevent firms from creating a hype about their IPO plans, chairman M. Damodaran said.

 New Delhi, July 21: The Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission is peeved that Jet and Sahara did not inform it of the failure of their proposed merger. The commission has directed its investigative arm to file an updated report on the current situation.

 Mumbai, July 21: Bombay High Court today approved the amalgamation of Reliance Infocomm and seven group firms and demerger of Reliance Communications Infrastructure?s network division from Reliance Communications.




